		<description><![CDATA[<p>Our own Sandi Bragar and Randy Rae are featured in financial media sharing their views on managing wealth in today's society. <a href="http://aspiriant.com/fathom/inside-aspiriant/aspiriant-news-advice-volatility-personal-security/">more &#62;</a></p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://aspiriant.com/fathom/inside-aspiriant/aspiriant-news-advice-volatility-personal-security/">Aspiriant in the News: Advice on Volatility, Personal Security</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://aspiriant.com">Aspiriant The Leading Independent Wealth Management Firm</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Aspiriant’s wealth managers have made headlines recently in major business publications by offering advice and insight on the challenges of managing wealth in today’s society.</p>
<h2>Sandi Bragar featured in The Wall Street Journal</h2>
<p><img src="http://aspiriant.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/wallstreetjournal.jpg" alt="The Wall Street Jounral Logo" width="202" height="19" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1018" />Sandi Bragar, managing director in planning strategy and research, was profiled in the Wall Street Journal. In <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/helping-high-net-worth-clients-navigate-the-challenges-of-their-wealth-1522249201?mod=searchresults&#038;page=1&#038;pos=1" rel="noopener" target="_blank">“Helping High-Net-Work Clients Navigate the Challenges of their Wealth,”</a> she discusses raising wealthy children to be self-sufficient adults, diversity, 529 Plans and climbing Machu Pichu. Sandi is a principal in our San Francisco office.</p>
<p><i>“While wealth comes with obvious advantages, financial abundance can also create complexity.”</i> </p>
<p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/helping-high-net-worth-clients-navigate-the-challenges-of-their-wealth-1522249201?mod=searchresults&#038;page=1&#038;pos=1" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Read more</a> (paywall) about Sandi’s background and how she advises dealing with the complexity.</p>
<h2>Randy Rae interviewed by Investment Advisor</h2>
<p><img src="http://aspiriant.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/investment-advisor-magazine-logo.jpg" alt="Investment Advisor logo" width="202" height="40" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1262" />Randy Rae, a manager in investment strategy and research in our Silicon Valley office, joined other wealth managers analyzing the comeback of volatility in Investment Advisor’s <a href="https://www.thinkadvisor.com/2018/04/02/volatilitys-bite-returns/?slreturn=20180408133222" rel="noopener" target="_blank">&#8220;Volatility’s Bite Returns: What Now?&#8221;</a>. </p>
<p><i>Randy “agrees this year’s volatility isn’t different, although the move was ‘unusually swift.’ He adds that it’s ‘healthy for the markets.’”</i></p>
<p><a href="https://www.thinkadvisor.com/2018/04/02/volatilitys-bite-returns/?slreturn=20180408133222" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Read the full article</a> on ThinkAdvisor.</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://aspiriant.com/fathom/inside-aspiriant/aspiriant-news-advice-volatility-personal-security/">Aspiriant in the News: Advice on Volatility, Personal Security</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://aspiriant.com">Aspiriant The Leading Independent Wealth Management Firm</a>.</p>
